===Etymology 1===
{{etymid|ja|e}}
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|え}}

Change in meaning from {{ja-r|枝|え|pos=historically ''ye'', “[[branch]], [[stem]]”}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|え|acc=0|acc_ref=DJR}}
{{ja-accent-dialectal|region=Kyoto|k-0|えー|éé|ref=ZAJ}}
{{ja-accent-dialectal|region=Kagoshima|kt-a||え|ぇ|ê|ref=ZAJ}}

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|え}}

# a [[handle]], a [[grip]], a [[shaft]], a [[haft]]
#: {{syn|ja|取っ手|取手|把手|tr3=totte}}
#: {{ja-usex|[[大%鎌]]の'''柄'''|おお%がま の '''え'''|a [[snath]], a [[scythe]] shaft}}

=====Idioms=====
* {{ja-r|柄の無い所に柄をすげる|え の ない ところ に え を すげる}}: “to attach a handle where there isn't one” → to strain credibility with one's words, to [[talk out one's ass]]

===Etymology 2===
{{etymid|ja|kabi}}
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|かび|alt=穎}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|-|sort=かび}}. Used in the ''{{w|Kojiki}}''. Generally regarded as cognate with {{ja-r|黴|かび|[[mold]]}}, from the shared idea of [[sprout]]s or [[shoot]]s. Appears to be the noun stem of {{cog|ojp|-|sort=かび}} verb {{ja-r|かぶ}} (source of modern {{ja-r|黴る|かびる|to go [[moldy]]}}), with probable original meaning of {{m|en|sprout|to sprout}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|かび}}

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|かび}}

# {{lb|ja|sort=かび|archaic}} a [[sprout]]
#: {{syn|ja|芽|tr=me}}
# {{ja-def|穎}} {{lb|ja|sort=かび|archaic}} an [[ear]] of [[grain]], particularly of [[rice]]
#: {{syn|ja|穂|tr1=ho|穂先|tr2=hosaki}}
# {{lb|ja|sort=かび|archaic}} the [[handle]] or [[grip]] of a [[tool]], or [[hilt]] of a [[blade]] {{qualifier|by extension from the idea of “a smaller portion sticking out from the main body” like a sprout}}
#: {{syn|ja|柄|tr=tsuka}}

=====Usage notes=====
The {{m|en|grain}} sense is more commonly spelled {{l|ja|穎}}.

===Etymology 3===
{{etymid|ja|kai}}
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|かい|alt=穎}}

{{IPAchar|/kabi/}} → {{IPAchar|/kapi/}} → {{IPAchar|/kaɸi/}} → {{IPAchar|/kawi/}} → {{IPAchar|/kai/}}

Alteration of ''kabi''.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|かい}}

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|かい|hhira=かひ}}

# {{lb|ja|sort=かい|archaic}} the [[basis]] of something, the [[origin]] of something

===Etymology 4===
{{etymid|ja|kara}}
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|から}} <span id="particle"></span>

From {{inh|ja|ojp|-|sort=から}}, from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*kara}}. Origin of particle {{m|ja|から|tr=kara||from, because}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|から}}

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|から}}

# {{lb|ja|sort=から|archaic}} {{qualifier|by extension from the ''qualities'' sense}} an [[origin]] or [[source]], a [[reason]] for something

=====Usage notes=====
Often followed by the particle {{ja-r|に}}. This usage evolved into the modern particle {{m|ja|から|tr=kara||from, because}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

====Suffix====
{{ja-pos|suffix|から}}

# of the same [[lineage]]
# the inherent [[quality|qualities]] or [[characteristic]]s of a thing

=====Usage notes=====
The {{m|en|lineage}} sense is often found embedded in other words, such as the first few of the following.

=====Derived terms=====
{{col|ja
|{{sense|lineage}} {{ja-r|同胞|はらから}}: “of the (same) belly” → a [[sibling]], more specifically a sibling from the same [[mother]]
|{{sense|lineage}} {{ja-r|族|やから}}: “of the (same) house” → a [[family]] [[member]]
|{{sense|lineage}} {{ja-r|親族|うから}}: “of the (same) parents/ancestors” → a [[blood relative]]
|{{sense|qualities}} {{ja-r|神柄|かみから}}, {{ja-r|神柄|かむから}}: the [[true]] [[nature]] of a [[god]]
|{{sense|qualities}} {{ja-r|山柄|やまから}}: the [[nature]] or [[characteristic]]s of a [[mountain]]
}}

===Etymology 5===
{{etymid|ja|kara-2}}
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|から|alt=幹}}

In light of the {{m|en|stem}} sense, probably derived semantically from {{m|en|origin}}, {{m|en|source}} meanings.

Compare also {{cog|ko|가락}}, similarly used as a counter for long and slender objects.

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|から}}

====Counter====
{{ja-pos|counter|から}}

# used to count items with [[shaft]]s

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|から}}

# the [[trunk]] or [[stem]] of a [[plant]]
# the [[shaft]] of an [[arrow]]
# the [[shaft]], [[haft]], or [[handle]] of a [[tool]]

====Prefix====
{{ja-pos|prefix|から}}

# describes something with a [[stem]], [[shaft]], or [[handle]]

=====Usage notes=====
The {{m|en|shaft}} sense is often found embedded in other words, such as the following, which are often spelled with other kanji.

=====Derived terms=====
{{col|ja
|{{ja-r|柄臼|からうす|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|唐臼|からうす|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|碓|からうす}}: a kind of [[mortar]] and [[pestle]] with the pestle mounted on a long [[shaft]] for [[leverage]]
|{{ja-r|柄%秤|から%はかり|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|唐%秤|から%はかり|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|権%衡|から%はかり}}: a [[balance]] [[scale]] (as opposed to a [[spring]] scale)
|{{ja-r|柄%秤|から%ばかり|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|唐%秤|から%ばかり|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|権%衡|から%ばかり}}: same as above
|{{ja-r|柄楫|からかじ|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|唐楫|からかじ}}: a [[tiller]] with a [[shafted]] [[handle]]
|{{ja-r|柄鋤|からすき|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|唐鋤|からすき|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|犂|からすき}}: a [[plow]] (literally, “a [[spade]] on a long [[shaft]]”)
}}

===Etymology 6===
{{etymid|ja|gara}}
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|がら}}

Alteration of ''kara'', “qualities, characteristics”. Originally only found as a suffix. {{rendaku2|sort=がら|kara|gara}} The rendaku pronunciation was then later used independently.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|がら|acc=0|acc_ref=DJR}}

====Suffix====
{{ja-pos|suffix|がら}}

# the inherent [[quality|qualities]] or [[characteristic]]s of a thing
# a [[shape]], [[pattern]], or [[design]]

=====Derived terms=====
{{col|ja
|{{sense|qualities}} {{ja-r|随%神|かんな%がら}}: will of the gods; Shinto belief in harmony with the gods and nature
|{{sense|qualities}} {{ja-r|国%柄|くに%がら}}: a [[nation]]'s (good) qualities; the state of a nation
|{{sense|qualities}} {{ja-r|人%柄|ひと%がら}}: a person's [[character]]
|{{sense|qualities}} {{ja-r|家%柄|いえ%がら}}: a family's or household's [[station]] or [[standing]] in [[society]]
|{{sense|qualities}} {{ja-r|続%柄|つづき%がら|rom=-}}, {{ja-r|続き柄|つづきがら}}: one's [[immediate]] [[relation]]s, such as [[parent]]s or [[sibling]]s
|{{sense|qualities}} {{ja-r|場%所%柄|ば%しょ%がら}}: the qualities of a [[place]]; that which is [[appropriate]] or [[suitable]] for a place
|{{sense|qualities}} {{ja-r|時%節%柄|じ%せつ%がら}}: the qualities of a [[time]] or [[season]]; that which is [[appropriate]] or [[suitable]] for a time or season
|{{sense|shape}} {{ja-r|花%柄|はな%がら}}: a [[flower]] [[pattern]]
}}

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|がら}}

# one's [[physical]] [[shape]] or [[build]]
#: {{syn|ja|体付き|tr1=karadatsuki|体付|tr2=karadatsuki|なり|tr3=nari}}
#: {{ja-usex|'''柄'''の[[大きい]][[やつ]]だな。|'''がら''' の おおき.い やつ だ な。|Wow, he's sure '''built''' big.}}
# one's [[character]], [[personality]], or [[temperament]]
#: {{ja-usex|'''柄'''の[[悪い]][[人]]|'''がら''' の わるい ひと|a person with a bad '''character'''}}
# a [[pattern]] or [[design]], such as on [[cloth]]
#: {{syn|ja|模様|tr=moyō}}
#: {{ja-usex|あの'''柄'''は[[派手]][[過ぎる]]よ。|^あの '''がら''' は はで-すぎる よ。|That '''pattern''' is way too colorful.}}

=====Idioms=====
* {{ja-r|柄にもない|がら に も ない}}: “not even in one's character” → just not in one, just not suitable for one's character or abilities

===Etymology 7===
{{etymid|ja|tsuka}}
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|つか|alt=欛}}

Cognate with {{ja-r|束|つか|pos=ancient unit of length, equivalent to the amount covered from pinky to forefinger when gripping something; analogous to English {{m|en|hand}}}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

Both likely derive from verb {{ja-r|付く|つく|to [[set to]], to [[attach]], to [[accompany]]}}, particularly as seen in modern Japanese idioms such as {{ja-r|手を付ける|て を つける|to [[set]] one's [[hand]] to something}}, {{ja-r|手が付く|て が つく|lit=one's [[hand]] [[set on|sets on]] something|to [[start]] [[use|using]] something}}.

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|つか|acc=2|acc_ref=DJR}}

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|つか}}

# the [[hilt]] of a [[sword]] or [[knife]], or the [[grip]] of a [[bow]] or [[staff]]
# {{lb|ja|calligraphy|sort=つか}} the portion of a [[brush]] [[pen]] held in the hand
# a [[penis]]
#: {{syn|ja|Thesaurus:陰茎}}

=====Idioms=====
* {{ja-r|柄を握る|つか を にぎる}}: “to hold the grip” → to [[stay the course]] in a [[career]] or [[trade]] and become an old [[master]]
* {{ja-r|柄を取る|つか を とる}}: “to take the grip” → to [[stay the course]] in a [[career]] or [[trade]] and become an old [[master]]

===Etymology 8===
{{etymid|ja|tsuku}}
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|つく|alt=銑,釻}}

[[nominalization|Nominalization]] of verb {{ja-r|付く|つく|to [[attach]]}}.

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|つく}}

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|つく}}

# {{ja-def|柄|銑|釻}} the [[nock]] on either end of a [[bow#Noun|bow]] where the [[bowstring]] rests
# {{ja-def|柄|銑|釻}} a [[bent]] [[nail]] or other kind of [[spike]] attached to or driven through an iron [[staff]] or a [[truncheon]] to make the weapon more dangerous
# {{ja-def|柄|銑|釻}} the areas on either end of a [[yoke]] or other carrying [[pole]] where [[cordage]] or [[rope]] is attached, from which the [[load]] is carried
# {{ja-def|柄}} the [[grip]] of a [[tiller]], [[boathook]], or other [[pole]]
# {{ja-def|柄|銑|釻}} {{qualifier|as a pun on the verb sense of ''stick to, attach''}} a female [[entertainer]]'s or [[prostitute]]'s [[secret]] [[lover]]
